unciation assessment based on ''-th'' sound production during speaking activities.\"]}","{\"title\":\"Navigating the Business World: A Role-Playing Scenario\",\"objectives\":[\"Learn and practice using common business vocabulary.\",\"Improve the ability to hold longer, more complex conversations.\",\"Correctly use prepositions of time, place, and movement in business contexts.\",\"Reinforce correct pronunciation of words ending in ''-th''.\"],\"activities\":[\"Vocabulary Introduction (Visual/ReadWrite): Present a list of common business terms (e.g., ''stakeholder,'' ''profit margin,'' ''supply chain''). Use images and definitions. (10 minutes)\",\"Preposition Practice (ReadWrite): Complete fill-in-the-blank exercises focusing on prepositions of time, place, and movement in business contexts (e.g., ''The meeting is scheduled _for_ 2 PM,'' ''The office is located _in_ London,'' ''We are moving _towards_ a new strategy''). (10 minutes)\",\"Role-Playing (Speaking/Auditory): Simulate a business meeting scenario (e.g., a project update, a negotiation). The student takes on a specific role. Encourage the use of new vocabulary and correct prepositions. (20 minutes)\",\"Pronunciation Check (Auditory/Speaking): Focus on ''th'' sounds that may arise during the role-play. Provide immediate feedback and correction. (5 minutes)\",\"Feedback and Review (ReadWrite/Auditory): After the role-play, provide feedback on language use, fluency, and pronunciation. Focus on areas for improvement. (5 minutes)\"],\"materials\":[\"List of business vocabulary with definitions and example sentences\",\"Worksheet with preposition exercises\",\"Role-play scenario descriptions\",\"Business-related images or videos (optional)\",\"Feedback form\"],\"assessment\":[\"Observation of student''s language use and fluency during the role-playing activity.\",\"Assessment of preposition usage in written exercises and during speaking.\",\"Pronunciation assessment during role play.\"]}","{\"title\":\"Mastering the Past Perfect: Business Case Study Analysis\",\"objectives\":[\"Understand and correctly use the past perfect tense to describe completed actions before a specific point in the past.\",\"Further expand business vocabulary related to project management and problem-solving.\",\"Improve conversational fluency by discussing a complex business scenario.\",\"Refine ''-th'' pronunciation in longer sentences.\"],\"activities\":[\"Grammar Review (Visual/ReadWrite): Review the structure and usage of the past perfect tense. Compare it to the simple past and present perfect tenses. (10 minutes)\",\"Case Study Reading (ReadWrite/Auditory): Read a short business case study that involves a project failure. The case study should use the past perfect tense to explain the events leading up to the failure. (10 minutes)\",\"Discussion (Speaking/Auditory): Discuss the case study, focusing on the causes of the failure and the actions that had been taken before the failure occurred. Encourage the use of the past perfect tense. (15 minutes)\",\"Pronunciation Drill (Auditory/Speaking): Practice sentences from the case study with ''-th'' sounds, focusing on clear pronunciation and intonation. (5 minutes)\",\"Writing Activity (ReadWrite): Write a brief report summarizing the case study and explaining the key events using the past perfect tense. (10 minutes)\"],\"materials\":[\"Business case study (printed or digital)\",\"Worksheet with past perfect tense exercises related to the case study\",\"List of project management vocabulary\",\"Example report template\",\"Recording device (optional)\"],\"assessment\":[\"Observation of student''s use of past perfect tense in discussion and writing.\",\"Review of written report for correct tense usage and vocabulary.\",\"Pronunciation assessment based on ''-th'' sound production during discussion.\"]}"}', '{"AI Generated Lesson Plans"}', 'AI-generated lesson plans created on 6/9/2025', 'upcoming', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('cd90ab86-65b8-4b0e-8ce2-15ed38408f31', '5dd0d10c-b984-47bf-bcfa-f2f8245f60a5', '2025-06-10 04:23:27.791537+00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-06-10 04:23:27.791537+00', '2025-06-10 04:23:27.791537+00', 'c1c99ecd-5a36-4cfb-9fc2-80dd771c9689', '2025-06-10 04:23:27.189+00', '{"{\"title\":\"Perfecting the Present Perfect: A Business Case Study\",\"objectives\":[\"Accurately use the present perfect tense in spoken and written English.\",\"Expand business vocabulary related to achievements and project updates.\",\"Improve pronunciation of words ending in ''-th'' through targeted practice.\"],\"activities\":[\"Warm-up (5 mins): Review of simple past vs. present perfect using visual aids (timeline). Example: ''Yesterday, I finished the report.'' vs. ''I have finished the report.''\",\"Business Case Study (20 mins): Read a short case study about a company that has achieved significant success. Highlight sentences using the present perfect. Identify new business vocabulary and define them using a dictionary (readWrite).\",\"Present Perfect Practice (15 mins): Role-play a project update meeting. The student will use the present perfect to describe their accomplishments and challenges on a fictional project. Focus on correct tense usage and business vocabulary. Record the role-play for self-assessment (auditory).\",\"Pronunciation Drill (10 mins): Practice pronouncing words ending in ''-th'' (e.g., ''growth'', ''strength'', ''month'') using minimal pairs (e.g., ''thin'' vs. ''tin''). Use a mirror for visual feedback.\"],\"materials\":[\"Visual timeline illustrating the difference between simple past and present perfect.\",\"Short business case study document.\",\"List of business vocabulary words from the case study.\",\"Recording device (phone or computer).\",\"List of ''-th'' words and minimal pairs.\"],\"assessment\":[\"Monitor student''s use of the present perfect tense during the role-play.\",\"Evaluate pronunciation of ''-th'' sounds during the pronunciation drill.\",\"Review the recording of the role-play to identify areas for improvement.\"]}","{\"title\":\"Navigating Prepositions in Professional Communication\",\"objectives\":[\"Correctly use common prepositions in business contexts (e.g., ''in'', ''on'', ''at'', ''to'', ''for'', ''with'').\",\"Expand vocabulary related to workplace interactions and meetings.\",\"Develop conversational fluency by participating in structured discussions.\"],\"activities\":[\"Preposition Review (10 mins): Interactive exercise using online resources (visual and auditory) to review common prepositions and their usage. Focus on prepositions of time, place, and direction.\",\"Workplace Scenario (20 mins): Read a dialogue between colleagues discussing a project. Identify instances where prepositions are used. Rewrite sentences with incorrect prepositions. Discuss the nuances of different prepositions in similar contexts (readWrite).\",\"Meeting Simulation (20 mins): Simulate a short meeting where the student discusses a specific topic (e.g., marketing strategy, product development). Focus on using prepositions accurately and naturally. The tutor will provide prompts and feedback to encourage longer responses and address conversational fluency barriers.\",\"Wrap-up (5 mins): Identify 3 key takeaways regarding prepositions and workplace vocabulary.\"],\"materials\":[\"Online resources for preposition practice (e.g., interactive quizzes, videos).\",\"Dialogue script between colleagues.\",\"List of common prepositions and their uses.\",\"Prompts for the meeting simulation.\"],\"assessment\":[\"Observe student''s use of prepositions during the meeting simulation.\",\"Review student''s written corrections of preposition errors in the dialogue.\",\"Assess student''s ability to explain the correct usage of different prepositions.\"]}","{\"title\":\"Future Perfect & Perfect Continuous: Projecting Business Outcomes\",\"objectives\":[\"Understand and correctly use the future perfect and future perfect continuous tenses.\",\"Expand vocabulary related to forecasting, predictions, and long-term planning.\",\"Improve pronunciation of ''-th'' in more complex words (e.g., ''thirteenth'', ''strength'').\"],\"activities\":[\"Tense Introduction (10 mins): Introduce the future perfect and future perfect continuous tenses using visual aids (timelines) and examples related to business goals. Example: ''By next year, we will have launched the new product.'' vs. ''By next year, we will have been working on this project for three years.''\",\"Forecasting Exercise (20 mins): Present a hypothetical business scenario (e.g., a new marketing campaign). The student will write a short report (readWrite) predicting the outcomes using the future perfect and future perfect continuous tenses. The tutor will provide feedback on tense usage and vocabulary.\",\"Presentation Practice (15 mins): The student will present their forecast to the tutor, acting as a stakeholder. Focus on clear and concise communication, using the target tenses correctly. Record the presentation for self-assessment (auditory).\",\"Advanced ''-th'' Pronunciation (10 mins): Practice pronouncing more complex words containing the ''-th'' sound, focusing on stress and intonation. Use tongue twisters to improve articulation.\"],\"materials\":[\"Visual timelines illustrating the future perfect and future perfect continuous tenses.\",\"Hypothetical business scenario document.\",\"List of vocabulary related to forecasting and planning.\",\"Recording device.\",\"List of complex ''-th'' words and tongue twisters.\"],\"assessment\":[\"Evaluate student''s written forecast for correct tense usage and vocabulary.\",\"Assess student''s pronunciation and fluency during the presentation.\",\"Review the recording of the presentation to identify areas for further improvement.\"]}"}', '{"AI Generated Lesson Plans"}', 'AI-generated lesson plans created on 6/10/2025', 'upcoming', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('47601e9d-13fc-4d0c-84b0-05993168c6db', '5dd0d10c-b984-47bf-bcfa-f2f8245f60a5', '2025-06-10 13:15:17.138939+00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-06-10 13:15:17.138939+00', '2025-06-10 13:15:17.138939+00', 'c1c99ecd-5a36-4cfb-9fc2-80dd771c9689', '2025-06-10 13:15:16.895+00', '{"{\"title\":\"Perfecting Your Past: A Visual Timeline Adventure\",\"objectives\":[\"Understand and correctly use the present perfect tense.\",\"Differentiate between the simple past and present perfect tenses.\",\"Practice pronunciation of words ending in ''-th'' in context.\"],\"activities\":[\"**Visual Timeline Creation (15 mins):** Create a visual timeline of question''s life, focusing on significant achievements and experiences. For each event, write a sentence using both the simple past and present perfect tense. Example: ''I went to Paris in 2018.'' vs. ''I have been to Paris.'' Discuss the difference in meaning and usage.\",\"**Audio-Visual Correction (15 mins):** Play a short audio clip (news report or interview) containing examples of the present perfect and simple past. Question listens and identifies instances of each tense. Transcribe the sentences and focus on the correct pronunciation of words ending in ''-th'' (e.g., ''with'', ''through'').\",\"**''My Career Path'' Writing Exercise (20 mins):** Question writes a short paragraph about their ideal career path, using the present perfect to describe skills and experiences they have gained and the simple past for completed actions. Example: ''I have learned valuable skills in project management.'' ''I completed a marketing course last year.'' Focus on using correct prepositions in context related to career goals (e.g., ''interested in'', ''good at'').\"],\"materials\":[\"Whiteboard or large paper for timeline.\",\"Markers or pens.\",\"Audio clip with transcript.\",\"Writing prompts related to career goals.\"],\"assessment\":[\"Monitor timeline creation and provide immediate feedback on tense usage.\",\"Review the ''My Career Path'' paragraph for correct tense usage, preposition accuracy, and pronunciation of ''-th'' words.\"]}","{\"title\":\"Business Buzzwords & Preposition Power-Up!\",\"objectives\":[\"Expand business vocabulary related to meetings and presentations.\",\"Master the use of common prepositions in business contexts (e.g., ''in'', ''on'', ''at'', ''to'', ''for'', ''with'').\",\"Practice holding a short, structured business conversation.\"],\"activities\":[\"**Business Vocabulary Brainstorm & ReadWrite (15 mins):** Brainstorm business-related vocabulary. Introduce 10-15 new words related to meetings and presentations (e.g., ''agenda'', ''stakeholder'', ''deliverables'', ''pitch''). Write sentences using each word, focusing on context. Use a business article as a guide and find more words.\",\"**Preposition Practice with Visual Aids (15 mins):** Use visual aids (images of office scenes, charts, graphs) to practice using prepositions. Example: ''The report is on the desk.'' ''The meeting is at 2 PM.'' ''I am talking to the client.'' Create fill-in-the-blank exercises and discuss the correct usage. Pay special attention to prepositions commonly misused by B1 learners.\",\"**Role-Play: The ''Elevator Pitch'' (20 mins):** Question prepares and delivers a short ''elevator pitch'' for a hypothetical business idea. Focus on clear communication, correct preposition usage, and incorporating newly learned business vocabulary. Provide constructive feedback on content, delivery, and language accuracy.\"],\"materials\":[\"List of business vocabulary words.\",\"Visual aids (images, charts, graphs).\",\"Fill-in-the-blank exercises.\",\"Elevator pitch prompt.\"],\"assessment\":[\"Observe vocabulary usage and preposition accuracy during the role-play.\",\"Review the written sentences for vocabulary and preposition correctness.\"]}","{\"title\":\"The Perfect Presentation & Thorough ''Th'' Pronunciation\",\"objectives\":[\"Master the use of all perfect tenses (present, past, future).\",\"Improve pronunciation of words ending in ''-th'' through targeted exercises.\",\"Develop conversational fluency through a structured presentation activity.\",\"Learn business idioms and incorporate them into speech.\"],\"activities\":[\"**Perfect Tense Deep Dive (15 mins):** Review all three perfect tenses (present, past, future) with example sentences and explanations. Focus on the differences in meaning and usage. Create sentences using each tense based on personal experiences and future plans. Example: ''I will have finished my English course by next month.''\",\"**''Th'' Sound Drills & Minimal Pairs (15 mins):** Practice pronunciation of words ending in ''-th'' using minimal pair exercises (e.g., ''bath'' vs. ''bad''). Focus on tongue placement and airflow. Use a mirror to observe mouth movements. Record and listen to pronunciation to self-correct.\",\"**Presentation Practice: ''My Business Idea'' (20 mins):** Question prepares and delivers a short presentation about a business idea, incorporating perfect tenses, business vocabulary, and correct pronunciation of ''-th'' words. Encourage the use of a few business idioms (e.g., ''think outside the box'', ''touch base''). Provide detailed feedback on language, pronunciation, and presentation skills.\"],\"materials\":[\"List of perfect tense examples.\",\"Minimal pair exercise sheet.\",\"Mirror for pronunciation practice.\",\"Presentation prompt.\",\"List of common business idioms.\"],\"assessment\":[\"Evaluate the presentation for correct tense usage, pronunciation accuracy, and fluency.\",\"Provide specific feedback on areas for improvement.\"]}"}', '{"AI Generated Lesson Plans"}', 'AI-generated lesson plans created on 6/10/2025', 'upcoming', NULL, NULL, NULL),
