rsation: Debating Polish Foreign Policy Strategies", "category": "Conversation", "description": "Engage in a debate about different Polish foreign policy strategies, using conditional sentences and specialized vocabulary to support arguments."}, {"id": "subtopic_10", "level": "c1", "title": "Subject-Verb Agreement: Describing Legal Procedures", "category": "Grammar", "description": "Review subject-verb agreement rules and practice using them to describe legal procedures in Poland. Focus on accuracy in formal contexts."}, {"id": "subtopic_11", "level": "c1", "title": "Article Usage: Referring to Specific Laws and Institutions", "category": "Grammar", "description": "Practice using articles (a, an, the) correctly when referring to specific laws and legal institutions in Poland. Pay attention to nuances in meaning."}, {"id": "subtopic_12", "level": "c1", "title": "Vocabulary: The Structure of the Polish Court System", "category": "Vocabulary", "description": "Learn vocabulary related to the structure of the Polish court system, including ''Sąd Najwyższy'', ''Sąd Apelacyjny'', ''Sąd Okręgowy'', and ''Sąd Rejonowy''."}, {"id": "subtopic_13", "level": "c1", "title": "Pronunciation: Stress Patterns in Legal Terminology", "category": "Pronunciation", "description": "Practice stress patterns in multi-syllable legal terms to improve clarity and comprehension. Focus on common Polish legal terms used in English."}, {"id": "subtopic_14", "level": "c1", "title": "Conversation: Explaining a Polish Legal Case in Simple Terms", "category": "Conversation", "description": "Practice explaining a Polish legal case in simple terms to a non-expert audience, using correct grammar and appropriate vocabulary."}]'),
