nt sound (a book, a car). Use ''an'' before words starting with a vowel sound (an apple, an hour). Remember, it''s about the *sound*, not just the letter (a university).\n*   **The:** Use ''the'' when referring to something specific or already mentioned (The book on the table is mine). Also use ''the'' with unique things (the sun, the moon, the Eiffel Tower).\n*   **No Article:** Don''t use an article with plural nouns referring to things in general (I like cats) or with uncountable nouns (I drink water).\n\nCommon mistakes: Forgetting ''the'' when referring to something specific, or using ''a'' before a vowel sound.", "instruction": "Brief, clear explanation of the target grammar, with example sentences.", "content_type": "text", "ai_placeholder": "grammar_explanation", "instruction_bg_color_var": "secondary_bg"}, {"id": "example_dialogue", "type": "exercise", "title": "Example Dialogue", "instruction": "A short, simple conversation demonstrating the grammar in context.", "content_type": "full_dialogue", "ai_placeholder": "dialogue_content", "dialogue_lines": [{"text": "Hi David, did you read the book I lent you?", "character": "Maria"}, {"text": "Yes, Maria! It was a really good book. Thanks!", "character": "David"}, {"text": "Great! I''m glad you liked it. I found it at a bookstore near my house.", "character": "Maria"}, {"text": "Oh, I should visit that bookstore. I''m looking for an interesting novel.", "character": "David"}, {"text": "They have a wide selection. I think you''ll find something you like.", "character": "Maria"}, {"text": "Perfect! I''ll go there this weekend. Thanks for the recommendation!", "character": "David"}], "instruction_bg_color_var": "secondary_bg"}, {"id": "comprehension_practice_questions", "type": "exercise", "items": ["What did Maria lend David?", "Where did Maria find the book?", "What is David looking for?", "When will David visit the bookstore?", "Why is David going to the bookstore?"], "title": "Comprehension/Practice Questions"